---
import ProjectLayout from '../../layouts/ProjectLayout.astro';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, '');
---
<ProjectLayout
  title="Ogun SDI & LULC Mapping"
  year="2024–2025"
  section="GIS Project Management"
  category="GIS Project Manager · Sivan Design"
  tools={['GeoNode', 'GeoServer', 'PostGIS', 'QGIS', 'LULC Classification', 'System Integration', 'Capacity Building']}
>

  <section class="proj-section">
    <h2 class="proj-section-title">Background</h2>
    <div class="proj-body">
      <p>
        Ogun State needed a centralized, modern geospatial platform — plus a statewide Land Use/Land
        Cover (LULC) mapping deliverable on top of it — and a system its own team could run, extend
        and trust. Delivered by Sivan Design under the <strong>Ogun State Economic Transformation
        Project (OGSTEP)</strong> for the Ogun State Government, Nigeria, I served as <strong>GIS
        Project Manager</strong>: technical design, leading the development team, and the training
        that handed the platform to the Ogun SDI team.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="proj-section">
    <h2 class="proj-section-title">Methodology</h2>
    <ul class="proj-list">
      <li>Directed the design and deployment of an open-source SDI on <strong>GeoNode</strong>, <strong>GeoServer</strong> and <strong>PostGIS</strong>, hosted on the state's own VMs with <strong>OGC-compliant web services (WMS/WFS/WCS)</strong>.</li>
      <li>Directed design of the <strong>Geom Tool</strong> — an in-house app that lets surveyors upload survey data and semi-automatically generate cadastral parcel geometry, replacing slow manual digitization with an auditable workflow.</li>
      <li>Led design of the cadastral layers, a statewide <strong>Unique Parcel Identifier (UPI)</strong> framework, and a bi-directional integration between the SDI and <strong>OLARMS</strong> (the state's land-administration system).</li>
      <li>Directed the statewide <strong>LULC classification</strong>, combining <strong>Sentinel-2</strong> and high-resolution imagery with field ground control points and temporal change analysis.</li>
      <li>Designed and delivered hands-on training — GIS/QGIS basics, block-drawing, and Administrator Training that handed clear ongoing roles to the four-person Ogun SDI team.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="proj-section">
    <h2 class="proj-section-title">Screenshots</h2>
    <img
      src={`${base}/maps/ogun-sdi-web-map.jpg`}
      alt="Ogun SDI web-map portal showing the state's Local Government Areas highlighted in green with labels and a search bar"
      class="proj-map"
      loading="lazy"
    />
    <p class="proj-map-caption">
      The Ogun SDI web-map portal — a GeoNode-based geoportal giving the state government and the public a browsable view of Ogun's spatial data, including its Local Government Areas.
    </p>
    <img
      src={`${base}/maps/ogun-sdi-imagery.jpg`}
      alt="High-resolution aerial imagery of an Ogun State settlement showing buildings, roads and farmland used as the basis for LULC classification"
      class="proj-map"
      loading="lazy"
    />
    <p class="proj-map-caption">
      High-resolution imagery covering the state — the raw input layered with Sentinel-2 data and ground control points to produce the statewide LULC classification.
    </p>
    <img
      src={`${base}/maps/ogun-sdi-training.jpg`}
      alt="Administrator training session in progress, with the Ogun SDI team and Sivan Design staff working at laptops around a conference table"
      class="proj-map"
      loading="lazy"
    />
    <p class="proj-map-caption">
      The Administrator Training session — handing the platform over to the Ogun SDI team, role by role.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="proj-section">
    <h2 class="proj-section-title">Project Link</h2>
    <p class="proj-body">
      The Ogun SDI geoportal is live and publicly accessible.
    </p>
    <a class="proj-external proj-external-primary" href="https://gis.ogunstate.gov.ng/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
      Open Ogun SDI →
    </a>
  </section>

</ProjectLayout>

<style>
  :global(.proj-list) {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 10px;
    max-width: 68ch;
  }
  :global(.proj-list li) {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: #2A2A2A;
    padding-left: 1.2em;
    position: relative;
  }
  :global(.proj-list li::before) {
    content: '—';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: #3D5E35;
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .proj-external {
    display: inline-block;
    margin-top: 12px;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #3D5E35;
    text-decoration: none;
  }
  .proj-external:hover { text-decoration: underline; }
  .proj-external-primary {
    padding: 10px 20px;
    color: #F0EAE0;
    background: #3D5E35;
    border-radius: 4px;
    transition: background 0.15s;
  }
  .proj-external-primary:hover { background: #2E4828; text-decoration: none; }
</style>
